  "2026-05-10T08:47:54.924Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: implemented forgiving repeatable-entry parsing for create/update/files/docs/test so bare dependency IDs infer kind=related, bare file/doc paths infer path with project scope, bare linked test values infer command, and rich comment/note/learning seeds with extra key-like metadata are preserved as text instead of failing and causing lossy retries. Verification passed: temp project end-to-end dogfood with isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH; pm linked tests passed including coverage 90 files/1252 tests at 100%; focused command suite 129 tests passed; pnpm quality:static passed; scripts/check-secrets passed. pm validate and pm health still report only the pre-existing history drift warnings on pm-54d, pm-f3q4, pm-fdla, pm-mb4n, and pm-tq1."
